79 "16-11-114.
80 (a) As used in this Code section, the term '3D printed firearm' means any weapon produced
81 by means of three-dimensional printing from computer-aided design files which is designed
82 or intended to propel a missile of any kind and which is not produced subject to a license
83 from the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives of the United States
